definitions.definition: An early termination of a mission, action, or procedure in relation to missiles or spacecraft; the craft making such a mission.
examples: We've had aborts on three of our last seven launches.

definitions.definition: The function used to abort a process .
An event in which a process is aborted.
examples: We've had three aborts over the last two days.

definitions.definition: The product of a miscarriage; an aborted offspring; an abortion .
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the early 17 century.

definitions.definition: A miscarriage ; an untimely birth; an abortion .
definitions.dating_raw: Attested from around (1350 to 1470) until the mid 17 century.

main_definition: ( military , aeronautics ) An early termination of a mission, action, or procedure in relation to missiles or spacecraft; the craft making such a mission.
secondary_definitions: ( computing ) The function used to abort a process .
( computing ) An event in which a process is aborted.
( now rare ) The product of a miscarriage; an aborted offspring; an abortion . [First attested in the early 17 century.]
( obsolete ) A miscarriage ; an untimely birth; an abortion . [Attested from around (1350 to 1470) until the mid 17 century.]
